        <h3>HTML (HyperText Markup Language)</h3>
        <div class="concept-content">
          <img src="path/to/your/image.jpg" alt="HTML Illustration" class="concept-img">
          <p>HTML is the backbone of web pages. It provides the structure and content of a website, such as headings, paragraphs, images, and links. Think of HTML as the framework that organizes your web content.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <article class="concept">
        <h3>CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)</h3>
        <div class="concept-content">
          <img src="path/to/your/image.jpg" alt="CSS Illustration" class="concept-img">
          <p>CSS is what makes your website look visually appealing. It controls the layout, colors, fonts, and overall design of a web page. By separating style from structure, CSS allows developers to make changes efficiently.</p>
